Penguin Skis! This is one of my favourite games on Android. Ski Safari is so addictive, never gets boring and brings a new meaning to 'Casual' mobile gaming. It is so highly polished, from the animated backgrounds and fine attention to detail, to the catchy music and superb sound effects. The game starts from the title screen, where a cascading avalanche rudely awakes your character from his slumber, with his bed literally sliding down the mountain‚Ä¶Excellent! The gameplay is simple (just tap anywhere on the screen to jump, holding to backflip) and it is very satisfying, especially when soaring off a mountain and through the clouds, to finally come down for a perfect landing on the random slopes. There are boosts along the way to aid your attempt, such as hitching a lift on the back of a penguin or yeti, riding a snowmobile or being grabbed mid-air by a swooping eagle. However, the end is imminent and you actually feel sorry for your little skier Sven when he finally meets his doom with the falling avalanche. Awesome.

Ski Safari takes a relatively simple concept and packs it with details, many of which are unnecessary, but add personality and texture to the experience. Few games create that "just one more game" reaction as well as this one does.

This game, along with Reaper: Tale of a Pale Swordsman, are the two most beautiful looking games out there. I bet they were even made on the same game engine, cause they sure look about the same. The levels are really well made, and they even have a new  level with Dinosaurs. I love how you can play the North pole, and if you run into 3 raindeers the third one becomes Rudolf and you can glide through the air. I got this game on a whim, and I'm SO glad I did, as it's now my go to game for killing time. You'll spend hours on this upgrading different things and trying to get your top score on each different level. They even have a Halloween level. I could go on and on about it. But hey, 5 STARS ALL THE WAY! Controls work great on my Shield by the way, really easy to map.

First of all, it loads up the defiant ape logo, then one of three things happens: 1: It logs into Google play then just freezes on the monkey.  2: It logs into Google play, then the sleigh comes across at about 1 frame every 2 minutes then crashes. 3: If no wifi or in airplane mode, it doesn't log into Google Play Services of course, but immediately force closes. I've clicked report about 30 times.  This is on a stock, unrooted, up to date HTC Evo 3D with 280Mb free RAM and 12Gb free SD.  Worse still, as a last resort, I tried deleting the app and re-installing. I know for sure that it definitely backed up my progress to Google Play as I was able to see my comparative progress on all slopes.  But when I re-installed, on the one successful time I managed to log in and run the game, even though it said I was logged in to Google Play, I had zero coins and progress.  I tried contacting the developer over a month ago and offered to post diagnostic info and help resolve. They haven't bothered to get back to me.  I'll re-rate this up to a 5 star when they get back to me and my progress is restored.

This is the most fun I've had had on my tablet EVER!  Thhe controls are very easy.  Tap anywhere on the screen to jump, repeat tap to get up (the quicker the taps the better), and tap-hold to do back-flips, steer the eagle, and other special moves.  There are also some special power-ups you can use by tapping on their icons (boost, rocket).  You can also buy (for coins) other special add-ons (get up faster, pick up coins easier).  You can buy all kinds of other accessories too, both functional and cosmetic.  All in-app purchases are made with coins, which you earn while playing, or if you are impatient (like me), you can buy them with actual money.  The price for the coins seems very reasonable: 75,000 for $2.49US, which is enough for both expansion packs (Halloween and Christmas), with plenty left over for rockets, boosters, coin magnet, new scarfs & rides, and more.  The video demonstrates the basic game play. Every run down the slope you're given 3 challenges (back-flip on a yeti, catch 3 penguins mid-air, etc.).  When you meet a challenge, it's taken off your list, and you earn a star.  Collect enough stars and you level-up, unlocking more slopes and bonuses.  Fun for all!

I've had this game for months and have advanced to the top level.  Now, it has slowed  to a crawl.  Turning wi-fi off did not resolve, nor did clearing the data (there is no cache to  clear!)  I did everything humanly possible on my tablet to get this game to run faster.  Impossible. Was reluctantly forced to uninstall and loose everything.    I would also like to add, its IMPOSSIBLE to collect TEN presents when you reach the upper levels.  Won't happen ever.  The later goals as you move way up are not going to be reachable.  Also, good luck flying an eagle through the cave.  My scores have reached the 2 million range, and those goals are unobtainable. I was never able to get that blasted pigeon through the cave because the icebergs simply hang too low and the bird cant fly.  Also the "real" one star reviews are moved way down the list, I only hope one person in a million will read this so they know what to expect as they advance levels and the game drags on.  ps I never bought coins there was no need.  This game does truly have an end-its when it slows to a crawl after months of playing it and the goals become impossible.  Thats when its time to move on to something else.

Ski Safari is a flawless game that just keeps getting better. The controls are simple, but the randomly generated slopes keep the game interesting. The only thing you have to do is jump (and flip if you want to get more boost). Mixed in each stage are animals that you can ride, or can catch a ride with you. and they help take damage when things get a bit too hectic. The halloween stage was a welcomed addition, and now the christmas one further improves gameplay. There are achievements, a plethora of unlockables, and in-app purchases if you feel the need to not put forth a little bit of effort and enjoy the game. I highly recommend this game to anyone who wants a simple, but addictive way to waste time.
